strings.Value: "Just think of it — hordes of barbarians, destroyed. Civilization and reason for once claiming victory over savagery and brute force. It almost makes me feel optimistic!"
"Don't be afraid for your own sake. — Pure bile runs in your veins instead of blood. This fate will surely spare you!"
"You disappoint me. Don't you see that victory has merely doomed us to further torment and trials, while the barbarians have found their eternal peace?"
"Civilization and order always prevail against savagery and chaos. They may lose a battle or two, but they win the war."
"In this game, the barbarians were only pawns. It's good that our kingdom's ruler saved us from the same lot."
